# Guest-bound files MUST check out with LF line endings: they are shipped
# byte-for-byte into the Alpine guest (Copy-VMFile), where busybox sh /
# OpenRC reject CRLF ("\r" reaches the interpreter as part of the line).
# This repo runs on Windows with core.autocrlf=true, which would otherwise
# rewrite these to CRLF on checkout — the same failure class the
# bundle.sha256 LF fix in launcher/guest_parser.py guards at runtime.
# (#655 Stage C; see docs/security/guest_parser_provisioning_record.md.)
scripts/guest/** text eol=lf

# Budgeted doctrine surfaces MUST check out with LF. Their byte budgets
# (tests/security/test_doctrine_freshness.py SIZE_BUDGETS) are measured on the
# working-tree file with stat().st_size, and were calibrated on LF content. On
# Windows with core.autocrlf=true these otherwise check out CRLF, adding one
# byte per line — enough to push CLAUDE.md (47,704 LF) over its 48,000 budget as
# 48,021 CRLF, failing the size gate on a clean checkout while the committed blob
# is fine. Pinning eol=lf removes the platform variable so the gate is
# deterministic (structural-absence over a hope-the-tree-is-LF configuration).
# Surfaced 2026-07-23 by the #1067 doctrine-figure merge; the handoff brief had
# flagged it as "worth its own ticket".
CLAUDE.md text eol=lf
docs/TEST_GOVERNANCE.md text eol=lf
docs/sprints/ACTIVE_SPRINT.md text eol=lf
.github/copilot-instructions.md text eol=lf
LESSONS.md text eol=lf
